x64 version of rip-record released 


17/12/16

Removed the need for  creation of desktop short cut 
combined installer into 1 32/64 bit installer 

18/12/2016


there was an error in v 1.5  installer was attempting to install to directory c:/programfiles(x86)Rip-record

this error has now been fixed abd the installer is now  installing into the correct directory 

30/12/2016

update to speed up install process Rip-Record now contains all files within its own directory and auto configures git

Note 1.8 is a major upgrade from 1.6  and a complete uninstall of rip-record  with version numbers lower than 1.8 is mandatory
